# Nutino System Architecture Design

## 1. Context & Assumptions
Based on the provided details, Nutino is an intelligent news dashboard utilizing ReactJS, Express, MongoDB, Google Gemini Pro, and NewsAPI. 

**Assumptions made:**
- The system focuses on read-heavy operations (news viewing) with occasional write operations (saving articles, user registration).
- Caching is implemented on the backend to reduce calls to external APIs (NewsAPI/Gemini) due to rate limiting and cost.
- The system will be deployed to a cloud provider (e.g., AWS, GCP) using standard containerized deployment practices.
- Images and static assets from news articles will be served via their original sources, not mirrored on our servers.

---

## 2. High-Level Architecture (HLA) - C4 Level 1 Context

The context diagram illustrates Nutino and its interactions with users and external systems.

```mermaid
C4Context
    title System Context Diagram for Nutino

    Person(user, "User", "A reader of the Nutino dashboard who browses and saves news.")
    
    System(nutino, "Nutino System", "Intelligent AI-powered news dashboard.")
    
    System_Ext(newsapi, "NewsAPI", "Provides real-time global news headlines and articles.")
    System_Ext(gemini, "Google Gemini Pro API", "Provides AI-based 3-bullet point summarization.")
    
    Rel(user, nutino, "Views news, triggers summaries, saves articles", "HTTPS")
    Rel(nutino, newsapi, "Fetches news feeds by category", "REST/HTTPS")
    Rel(nutino, gemini, "Requests summaries of articles", "REST/HTTPS")
```

---

## 3. Container-Level Architecture - C4 Level 2

This level breaks down Nutino into its primary deployable containers.

```mermaid
C4Container
    title Container Diagram for Nutino

    Person(user, "User", "A reader.")

    System_Boundary(nutino, "Nutino System") {
        Container(web, "Web Application", "ReactJS, Tailwind CSS", "Provides the responsive single-page application interface.")
        Container(api, "API Gateway / Backend", "Node.js, Express", "Handles business logic, authentication, and routing.")
        ContainerDb(db, "Database", "MongoDB", "Stores user profiles, credentials, and saved articles.")
        Container(cache, "Session/Data Cache", "Redis (Recommended) / In-Memory", "Caches NewsAPI responses and Gemini summaries to minimize external API calls.")
    }

    System_Ext(newsapi, "NewsAPI", "External news provider.")
    System_Ext(gemini, "Gemini API", "AI summarization provider.")

    Rel(user, web, "Visits and interacts with", "HTTPS")
    Rel(web, api, "Makes API calls to", "JSON/HTTPS")
    Rel(api, db, "Reads from and writes to", "Mongoose/TCP")
    Rel(api, cache, "Reads/Writes cache", "TCP")
    Rel(api, newsapi, "Fetches live news", "HTTPS/REST")
    Rel(api, gemini, "Gets AI summaries", "HTTPS/REST")
```

**Responsibilities & Technologies:**
- **Web Application:** Renders UI, maintains client-side routing (React Router), and manages state.
- **API Backend:** Exposes RESTful endpoints, handles JWT generation/validation, interacts with MongoDB and external APIs.
- **Database:** Persistent storage for user data.
- **Cache:** Highly recommended to prevent exhausting NewsAPI limits and to ensure rapid response times for frequently viewed categories.

---

## 4. Component-Level Design - C4 Level 3 (API Backend)

Decomposition of the Node.js / Express backend service.

```mermaid
C4Component
    title Component Diagram for API Backend

    Container_Boundary(api, "API Backend Application") {
        Component(router, "Express Router", "Express", "Routes incoming requests to appropriate controllers.")
        Component(authCtrl, "Auth Controller", "Node.js", "Handles registration, login, JWT signing.")
        Component(newsCtrl, "News Controller", "Node.js", "Manages news fetching and category filtering.")
        Component(summaryCtrl, "Summary Controller", "Node.js", "Prompts Gemini for article summaries.")
        Component(userCtrl, "User Controller", "Node.js", "Manages saved articles and user profiles.")
        Component(dbService, "Mongoose Models", "Mongoose", "Object Data Modeling for MongoDB.")
        Component(cacheService, "Cache Manager", "Node.js", "Checks for existing responses before calling external APIs.")
    }

    ContainerDb(db, "MongoDB", "Database", "Data storage.")
    System_Ext(newsapi, "NewsAPI", "News Source.")
    System_Ext(gemini, "Gemini API", "AI Source.")
    Container(web, "Web Application", "React", "Frontend.")

    Rel(web, router, "API Requests")
    Rel(router, authCtrl, "/api/auth/*")
    Rel(router, newsCtrl, "/api/news/*")
    Rel(router, summaryCtrl, "/api/summarize/*")
    Rel(router, userCtrl, "/api/user/*")
    
    Rel(authCtrl, dbService, "Uses")
    Rel(userCtrl, dbService, "Uses")
    
    Rel(newsCtrl, cacheService, "Checks cache")
    Rel(summaryCtrl, cacheService, "Checks cache")
    
    Rel(cacheService, newsapi, "Fetches if cache miss")
    Rel(cacheService, gemini, "Fetches if cache miss")
    
    Rel(dbService, db, "TCP")
```

---

## 5. Low-Level Design (LLD)

### Error Handling Flow
1. **Controller Layer:** Catches exceptions using `try/catch` blocks or express `asyncHandler`.
2. **Service Layer:** Throws custom operational errors (e.g., `NotFoundError`, `UnauthorizedError`).
3. **Global Error Middleware:** Captures all unhandled errors, formats them into a standard JSON response (`{ success: false, error: "message", stack: ... }` in Dev), and logs them to the console/monitoring system.

### Data Flow inside Services
- `Request` -> `Global Rate Limiter` -> `Auth Middleware (if protected)` -> `Validation Middleware (Joi/Zod)` -> `Controller` -> `Service (Business Logic)` -> `External API/DB` -> `Response formatting` -> `Client`.

---

## 6. API Design

### Authentication APIs
- **`POST /api/auth/register`**
  - **Body:** `{ "name": "John", "email": "j@test.com", "password": "..." }`
  - **Response:** `{ "token": "jwt_string", "user": { "id": "...", "name": "..." } }`
- **`POST /api/auth/login`**
  - **Body:** `{ "email": "j@test.com", "password": "..." }`

### News APIs
- **`GET /api/news/top-headlines?category=business&page=1`**
  - **Auth:** Oaptional
  - **Response:** `{ "articles": [{ "title": "...", "url": "...", "source": "..." }] }`
- **`POST /api/news/summarize`**
  - **Auth:** Required (Bearer Token)
  - **Rate Limit:** 5 requests per minute per user.
  - **Body:** `{ "articleUrl": "https://...", "articleContent": "..." }`
  - **Response:** `{ "summary": ["Point 1", "Point 2", "Point 3"] }`

### User APIs
- **`POST /api/user/saved-articles`**
  - **Auth:** Required
  - **Body:** `{ "article": { "title": "...", "url": "..." } }`
- **`GET /api/user/saved-articles`**
  - **Auth:** Required
  - **Response:** `{ "savedArticles": [...] }`

---

## 7. Database Design

```mermaid
erDiagram
    USERS {
        ObjectId _id PK
        string name
        string email "Unique, Indexed"
        string password_hash
        datetime createdAt
    }
    SAVED_ARTICLES {
        ObjectId _id PK
        ObjectId user_id FK "Indexed"
        string title
        string url
        string source_name
        string image_url
        string ai_summary "Optional"
        datetime savedAt
    }
    
    USERS ||--o{ SAVED_ARTICLES : "bookmarks"
```

**Indexing Strategy:**
- `USERS.email`: Unique index for fast login lookups and preventing duplicates.
- `SAVED_ARTICLES.user_id`: Index for quickly retrieving a user's dashboard of saved items.

